abstract: LogMeIn, a software maker whose investors include the chip giant Intel, priced its initial public offering at the top of the expected range late Tuesday.
snippet: LogMeIn, a software maker whose investors include the chip giant Intel, priced its initial public offering at the top of the expected range late Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: Update | 1:06 p.m. In what may be another positive sign for venture-backed companies hoping to go public, shares of LogMeIn rose as much as 30 percent in their first day on the Nasdaq, after pricing at the top of the expected range.

headline.main: LogMeIn’s Stock Surges in Nasdaq Debut
